                            <comment id="428448" author="qian_wc" created="Thu, 19 Sep 2024 01:59:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was thinking about the combination of soft sync and full sync.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the problem is how to determine that we need a soft sync from a client?&lt;br/&gt;
VFS does not provide enough information for this when memcg is under memory pressure...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="428442" author="adilger" created="Thu, 19 Sep 2024 00:37:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What happens if cgroups is not active?  It seems like a similar mechanism is still needed to trigger sync writes as memory pressure increases on the client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMHO, a combination of OBD_BRW_SOFT_SYNC (to start &quot;early commit&quot; if OST can be responsive enough) and then fully sync writes (to avoid client OOM if it is really low) would be best.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally, clients would adapt and start sending SOFT_SYNC writes with enough time for the OSTs to commit and clients start getting commits back before hitting fully sync writes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
